HEADWORD: Omniety
<hw>Om*ni"e*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which is
all-pervading or all-comprehensive; hence, the Deity.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Omniety</qex> formed nullity into an essence.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Omnifarious</ent>⟦br⟧
